name: Dionysus
description: Dionysus; Also called Bromios, Euhios, Dithyrambos, Iakkhos or Iobakkhos in some mythological works and especially in tragedies, the wine god of Çallı, also known as Bacchus in Roman mythology. It represents not only the intoxication of wine, but also its social and beneficial effects. He is a supporter of civilization and a lover of peace.
